description:
Time of Birth
Time of birth in 24-hour format. Midnight has a value of '24', any time after midnight but before 1 am has a value of '00'. Prior to mid-1992, out of state occurrences were not coded.
Mother's State of Residence (old NCHS code)

Infant's Calculated Ethnicity
The ethnicity code given here is from the NCHS algorithm which uses mother's and father's Hispanic ethnicity to derive a code for the child's Hispanic ethnicity.

Note: Hispanic ethnicity data are not complete for 1988. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Race/Hispanic Origin (Mother, Father, Child)."
Mother's Race Literal 1, American Indian/Alaska Native
Mother's Race Literal 2, American Indian/Alaska Native
Mother's Race Literal 1, Other Pacific Islander
Mother's Race Literal 2, Other Pacific Islander

Mother's Race
Uses race assigned by NCHS bridging methods (see Data Quality Technical Notes for description).
Mother's Hispanic Origin, Other Hispanic Literal

Mother's Hispanic Origin
Note: Hispanic ethnicity data are not complete for 1988. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Race/Hispanic Origin (Mother, Father, Child)."

Mother's Occupation - Milham
Sam Milham occupation codes are obtained from a computer program which uses the occupation and industry literal fields. This program coded about 93-97% of the records; the remaining 3-7% need to be hand-coded. The hand coding has not been done for 1993-present and for a portion of the 1992 cords. For further information please see the "Data Quality Technical Notes - Occupation (Milham Codes - other, Father)." For code table see ASCII file "occmil.asc". Note: there are codes on the file which are invalid.

Mother's Education Level
Highest grade completed by the mother.
Mother's Education Years If LE 8th Grade

Father's Age
Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Age
Father's Race Literal 1, American Indian/Alaska Native
Father's Race Literal 2, American Indian/Alaska Native
Father's Race Literal 1, Other Pacific Islander
Father's Race Literal 2, Other Pacific Islander

Father's Race Calculation
Uses race assigned by NCHS bridging methods (see Data Quality Technical Notes for description).
Father's Hispanic Origin, Other Hispanic Literal

Father's Hispanic Origin
Note: Hispanic ethnicity data are not complete for 1988. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Race/Hispanic Origin (Mother, Father, Child)."

Father's Occupation - Milham
Sam Milham occupation codes are obtained from a computer program which uses the occupation and industry literal fields. This program coded about 93-97% of the records; the remaining 3-7% need to be hand-coded. The hand coding has not been done for 1993-present and for a portion of the 1992 records. For further information please see the "Data Quality Technical Notes - Occupation (Milham Codes - Mother, Father)." For code table see ASCII file "occmil.asc". Note: there are codes on the file which are invalid.

Father's Education Level
Highest grade completed by the father.
Father's Education Years If LE 8th Grade

Weight Prior to Pregnancy
Number of pounds Mother weighed before pregnancy. Only whole number is kept. This field was first collected in 1992. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Weight Gained During Pregnancy, Prepregnancy Weight and Delivery Weight."

Mother's Weight At Delivery
Number of pounds Mother weighed at delivery. Only whole number is kept. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Weight Gained During Pregnancy, Prepregnancy Weight and Delivery Weight."

Weight Gain During Pregnancy
Number of pounds Mother gained during pregnancy. Only whole number is kept. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Weight Gained During Pregnancy, Prepregnancy Weight and Delivery weight." 
 
***2003-present***
This field is calculated from prepregnancy and delivery weights (see fields 110 and 213).
098 – 98+ lbs for out of state occurrences only
Number Cigarettes Smoked 3 Months Before Preg
Packs of Cigarettes Smoked 3 Months Before Preg
Packs of Cigarettes Smoked during 1st Trimester
Packs of Cigarettes Smoked during 2nd Trimester
Packs of Cigarettes Smoked during 3rd Trimester

Delivery Source of Payment
Indicates principal source of payment for the delivery.

WIC Benefits
Indicates whether the mother received WIC benefits during pregnancy. WIC (Women and Infant Children) is a free supplemental food and nutrition education program.

Month Prenatal Care Began
Indicates the month from the beginning of the pregnancy at which Mother entered prenatal care. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Month Prenatal Care Began." As of 
2003, this field is calculated from date of first prenatal visit and menses date.

NCHS Prenatal Care
NCHS method of calculation of prenatal care to file. Before using this field, see "data Quality Technical Notes – Month Prenatal Care Began."

Number of Prenatal Visits
Indicates the number of prenatal visits for the entire pregnancy. The ‘95' code was used until mid 1992.

Number of Prior Live Births, Now Living

Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Previous Pregnancy History."

Number of Prior Live Births, Now Dead
Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Previous Pregnancy History."

Gestation Estimate in Weeks
In weeks as estimated by the physician at the time of the delivery. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Gestational Age – Calculated and Clinical Estimate."

Calculated Gestation in Weeks
Calculated from the date of birth and last menses date (mensdate) or from gestational estimate. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes – Gestational Age – 
Calculated and Clinical Estimate."

Gestation, Calculated Flag
Indicates whether the calculated Gestation (gestcalc) field was calculated based on last menses date or estimated based on birth weight.
Medical Risk Factor, Previous Preterm Birth
Medical Risk Factor, Other Previous Poor Pregnancy Outcomes
Medical Risk Factor, Infertility Treatments, Drugs
Medical Risk Factor, Infertility Treatments, ART
Medical Risk Factor, Previous Cesarean Section
Medical Risk Factor, Number of Previous Cesarean Sections
Medical Risk Factor, Group B Strep
Medical Risk Factor, None of the Above
Maternal Infections, None of the Above
Obstetric Procedure, External Cephalic Version, Successful
Obstetric Procedure, External Cephalic Version, Failed
Obstetric Procedure, None of the Above
Onset of Labor, Premature Rupture of Membranes
Onset of Labor, None of the Above
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Induction of Labor
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Augmentation of Labor
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Non-vertex Presentation
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Anesthesia During Labor
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Steroids for Fetal Lung
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Antibiotics Received by Mother
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Chorioamnionitis Diagnosed
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Meconium Staining
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Fetal Intolerance of Labor
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, None of the Above
Characteristics of Labor and Delivery, Unknown
Maternal Morbidity, Admission to Intensive Care Unit
Maternal Morbidity, Unplanned Operating Room Procedure
Maternal Morbidity, None of the Above

Method of Delivery, Forceps Failed
Indicates whether forceps delivery was attempted but unsuccessful.

Method of Delivery, Vacuum Extraction Failed
Indicates whether vacuum extraction delivery was attempted but unsuccessful.
Method of Delivery, Final Route and Method

Birth Weight of Baby - Grams
Indicates gram weight of infant. Pounds and ounces are converted as follows: grams = [(lbs*16)+oz]*28.3495267 (Rounded to the nearest gram)

In 1980-1991 data was stored in units of pounds and ounces. This data has been converted to grams. Since one ounce is equivalent to 28 grams, the converted data will cluster in multiples of 28 grams. For more detail see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Birth Weight."

APGAR Score - 5 Minute
The numerical sum of points given for heart rate, respirator effort, muscle tone, reflexes and color. Score taken at 5 minutes. Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes – Apgar Score (5 minutes)."

APGAR Score - 10 Minute
The numerical sum of points given for heart rate, respirator effort, muscle tone, reflexes and color. Score taken at 10 minutes. Only reported if 5 minute score is <6.
Abnormal Conditions of Newborn, Assisted Ventilation, Immediate
Abnormal Conditions of Newborn, Assisted Ventilation, Over 6 Hours
Abnormal Conditions of Newborn, NICU Admission
Abnormal Conditions of Newborn, Surfactant Replacement
Abnormal Conditions of Newborn, Antibiotics for Newborn Sepsis
Abnormal Conditions of Newborn, Birth Injury
Abnormal Conditions of Newborn, None of the Above
Congenital Malformations, Cyanotic Congenital Heart Disease
Congenital Malformations, Down Syndrome Karyotype Confirmed
Congenital Malformations, Down Syndrome Karyotype Pending
Congenital Malformations, Chromosomal Disorder Karyotype Confirmed
Congenital Malformations, Chromosomal Disorder Karyotype Pending
Congenital Malformations, None of the Above

Classification of Certifier
Before using this field, see "Data Quality Technical Notes - Attendant/Certifier Classification."
Indicates that the infant died by the age of 1 year. Before using this field, see Data Technical Notes - Infant Death Flag.
Name of the street data set used to geocode
Geocoded tract using old method of determining geocoded
Geocoded block group using old method of determining geocoded
